		<content:heading>General-purpose</content:heading>
	</header>
	
	<main>
		<p>A general-purpose programming language is one designed to be used for writing software in the widest variety of application domains. A general-purpose programming language has this status because it does not include language constructs designed to be used within a specific application domain.</p>
		
